References
==========

I have used and worked through many of the guides, courses and books listed above over the years. But I got many others from googling and looking for new high quality resources. The following were helpful and may be updated long after I've stopped updating this guide:

- https://hackr.io/tutorials/learn-python

  A great community currated list of online resources to learn Python. Very likely to stay up to date.

- https://www.quora.com/What-is-the-best-online-resource-to-learn-Python

  The ever helpful Quora. I'm sure there are many other pages about Python, but this one helped me with this guide.



